This paper deals with the problem of interference in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and algorithms (cs.AL). The proposed algorithms involve optimization and connectivity predicates, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents experimental results, which could be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
